name: acor
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "acor" %}
{% set version = "1.1.1" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/acor-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 4c647d30326004cfcfbcf630e97586ce574954e36bebf75b657d33d5d79e94e3

build:
  number: 4
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
  host:
    - numpy
    - pip
    - python
  run:
    - python
    - {{ pin_compatible('numpy') }}

test:
  imports:
    - acor
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: http://github.com/dfm/acor
  summary: Estimate the autocorrelation time of a time series quickly.
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE.md

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - ickc
